Sales Executive (Arabic Speaker)
Confidential Company - ,
Date Posted: 2014/05/06 11:18:43
Ref. JB3047851
Job Description
The Role
This is a hands-on exhibition sales role to rebook current exhibitors, increase the amount they spend with us, and generate new business by handling incoming leads and sourcing new potential customers.
•	To be responsible for local stand sales for the portfolio and achieve agreed sales targets.
•	To rebook existing clients and maximise revenue
•	To seek out, consider and evaluate new business opportunities
•	To successfully close incoming sales enquiries
•	Sell exhibition space in accordance with set targets to ensure the revenue budget is achieved and exceeded.
•	Regularly and frequently review and monitor competitive publications/exhibitions and identify new leads to ensure that sales opportunities are developed and maximised.
•	Visit exhibitions and other events in order to make contact with current clients and develop relations with potential clients.
Skills
The Person
•	Arabic speaker required
•	Ability to work under pressure and to deadlines
•	Ability to prioritise tasks to meet sales and event objectives
•	Creative and lateral thinker - ability to generate ideas to improve sales
•	Analytical skills - competitor and market analysis
•	Self starter who is self motivated to achieve results
•	Positive attitude and able to overcome objections
